Yemen Wants Enhanced Economic Ties With China ,
SANAA , November 21 ( Xinhua ) -- Yemen foresees a bright future for its cooperation with China , particularly in the economic fields , said a Yemeni leader here Saturday .
Cheif of the Yemeni Consultative Council Abdul-Aziz Abdul-Ghani made the remark when meeting the visiting delegation of the Chinese People 's Association for Friendship with Foreign Countries .
He expressed his appreciation to the support China has rendered to Yemen 's construction and development .
The prospects of the Yemeni-Chinese ties are bright , Abdul-Ghani said , urging for more Chinese investments , especially in the Aden free trade zone .
He also pointed out the importance of the successful visit paid to China by Yemeni President Ali Abdullah Saleh early this year that led to the signing of a series of fruitful accords in various areas .
The Chinese delegation , led by the friendship association 's deputy president Su Guang , arrived here on November 16 for a ten-day visit to Yemen .
